{{multiple issues| {{notability|date=April 2013}}{{Cleanup-school|date=April 2013}}{{primary sources|date=April 2013}} }} '''MAPS College''' (formerly the '''MAPS Institute''' or the '''Modern Academy for Professional Studies''') is a private educational institution located in Janavaree Magu, [[Malé]], Maldives.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTSOUTHASIA/Resources/Human_capital_for_a_knowledge_society_higher_education_in_the_Maldives.pdf |title=Human capital for a knowledge society - higher education in the Maldives], World Bank reference |date=2011 |accessdate=3 April 2013}}</ref>
==MAPS College== The College was founded in 1999, and awarded college status in 2011. It provides post-secondary courses in accounting, finance, management, hospitality, and technology. In 2011, the institution moved to a new campus.
The College is operated by MAPS Maldives Private Ltd, a subsidiary of the [[FALIM Group]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.falim.com.mv/falim-structure.php |title=Falim structure |publisher=FALIM Group |accessdate =20 March 2013}}</ref>
== MAPS International High == '''MAPS International High''' is a senior [[high school]] that was established in 2011 by MAPS College.<ref>[http://www.maps.edu.mv/?p=2202 MAPS College and MAPS International High conducts information session in Raa Atoll], retrieved March 23, 2013</ref> It accepts students in grades 11 and 12, and offers [[GCE Advanced Level]] training and [[Edexcel]] Alevel and Edexcel International Diplomas.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mapsihigh.edu.mv/?page_id=85 |title=Study Options|publisher=MAPS International High |accessdate =20 March 2013}}</ref>
